---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<Layout
	title="Booking Terms & Conditions"
	description="Booking terms and conditions for Balance Performance Physiotherapy."
>
	<PageHero
		title="&amp; Conditions"
		highlight="Terms"
		breadcrumb="Terms &amp; Conditions"
	/>
	<section class="rich-content">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Balance Performance Physiotherapy Clinic Terms and Conditions</h2>

			<h3>Appointments</h3>
			<p>All Initial appointments must be paid in advance. If you are claiming through Axa or Bupa you will be asked for a current debit or credit card which we will held by stripe to cover any excess or shortfall that your insurance company tells us is your liability. We will inform you when we take these payments.</p>
			<p>Patients are advised to arrive on time to ensure they receive the full duration of their scheduled session.</p>

			<h3>Cancellations and Missed Appointments</h3>
			<p>A minimum of 24 hours' notice is required for any cancellation or rescheduling.</p>
			<p>Appointments cancelled with less than 24 hours' notice, or failure to attend, may result in the full appointment fee being charged.</p>
			<p>This time is extended to 48 hours' notice for Vojta Therapy.</p>

			<h3>Late Arrivals</h3>
			<p>Patients arriving late may have their session shortened to avoid disruption to other appointments.</p>
			<p>The full session fee will still apply.</p>

			<h3>Fees and Payment</h3>
			<p>Payment is due at the time of treatment unless otherwise agreed.</p>
			<p>We accept the following payment methods: Credit or Debit card, Bacs.</p>
			<p>Any outstanding balances must be cleared prior to booking further appointments.</p>

			<h3>Insurance Claims</h3>
			<p>Patients intending to claim through private health insurance are responsible for confirming their level of cover prior to treatment with their insurance provider.</p>
			<p>Any shortfall between the treatment fee and the insurance reimbursement remains the responsibility of the patient.</p>
			<p>Receipts and invoices can be provided upon request.</p>

			<h3>Consent to Treatment</h3>
			<p>By attending an appointment, patients provide consent to assessment and treatment by a qualified clinician.</p>
			<p>Patients have the right to withdraw consent at any time.</p>

			<h3>Medical Information</h3>
			<p>Patients must provide accurate and complete information regarding their medical history and current condition.</p>
			<p>If you have been referred by a GP or Consultant we require your referral letter or medical report a minimum of 48 hours prior to your appointment when possible, so your clinician can read it before your session and you can get the most from your time with them.</p>
			<p>Failure to disclose relevant information may affect the safety and effectiveness of treatment.</p>

			<h3>Confidentiality and Data Protection</h3>
			<p>All personal data, including payment information and card details, is handled in accordance with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>
			<p>Patient information will be kept confidential and only shared where necessary for treatment or when legally required.</p>

			<h3>Safeguarding and Chaperones</h3>
			<p>Patients may request a chaperone for any treatment session.</p>
			<p>The clinic adheres to appropriate safeguarding policies.</p>

			<h3>Treatment Outcomes</h3>
			<p>While physiotherapy aims to improve symptoms and function, no guarantees can be made regarding treatment outcomes.</p>

			<h3>Liability</h3>
			<p>The clinic and its practitioners hold appropriate professional indemnity insurance.</p>
			<p>Liability is limited to the extent permitted by law.</p>

			<h3>Complaints Procedure</h3>
			<p>If you are dissatisfied with any aspect of your care, please contact the clinic directly.</p>
			<p>All complaints will be addressed promptly and in accordance with the clinic's complaints procedure.</p>

			<h3>Amendments to Terms and Conditions</h3>
			<p>The clinic reserves the right to update these Terms and Conditions at any time.</p>
			<p>The latest version will always be available upon request.</p>

			<p style="margin-top:32px;">If you'd like to view our privacy policy please see <a href="/privacy-policy">our privacy policy page</a>. For any queries about these terms, please email <a href="mailto:admin@balancephysio.com">admin@balancephysio.com</a> or call <a href="tel:02076272308">020 7627 2308</a>.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
